<section class="hero">

<h1>
Prote<span>omics</span>
</h1>

<p>
Proteomics investigates the complete set of proteins expressed within biological systems. By studying protein abundance, structure, interactions, signaling pathways, and post-translational modifications, proteomics reveals the functional machinery driving cellular biology, disease mechanisms, and therapeutic discovery.
</p>

<div class="hero-image">
  <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
    <source src="/Proteomics overview infographic.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
</div>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
What is <span>Proteomics?</span>
</h2>

<div class="infographic">

  <img
    src="/1_Proteomics.png"
    alt="Proteomics overview infographic"
  >

</div>

<p>
Proteomics is the study of the full protein complement of cells, tissues, or organisms. Proteins carry out many of the biological functions encoded by genes and regulated by cellular systems.
</p>

<p>
Modern proteomics uses mass spectrometry, protein interaction analysis, pathway mapping, and computational biology to understand cellular function, disease mechanisms, biomarkers, and therapeutic targets.
</p>

